IT Budget




Agrium Inc. headquartered in Calgary, AB is a global marketer, producer and distributor, wholesale and retail, of agricultural products and services. They have operations spanning North and South America, Europe, and Asia-Pacific.

PotashCorp. is in the process of merging with Agrium… MoreAgrium Inc. headquartered in Calgary, AB is a global marketer, producer and distributor, wholesale and retail, of agricultural products and services. They have operations spanning North and South America, Europe, and Asia-Pacific.

PotashCorp. is in the process of merging with Agrium Inc.  The deal will need to clear regulatory and shareholder review in the US and Canada.  
IT Priorities:
• Migrating data from legacy systems to a third party vendor.
• The company has plans to invest much of its budget for 2013 maybe 2014 on IT security in the areas of policy compliance, enforcement mobile security storage, and security… MoreIT Priorities:
• Migrating data from legacy systems to a third party vendor.
• The company has plans to invest much of its budget for 2013 maybe 2014 on IT security in the areas of policy compliance, enforcement mobile security storage, and security contingency
• Expecting IT infrastructure spending and expenditures to increase in data storage, network performance, remote access control, and data center. 
• Indicates increase spending in supply chain, in the areas of improving polices, purchasing process, sales and operations planning process.

IT Structure:

• The company's corporate headquarters in Calgary, AB serves as the IT hub and main data center location for the global firm.
• IT Shared Services for Agrium oversees the cross-functional IT operation of Wholesale, Retail and Advanced Technology business units. 
• Agrium Inc. built a new 2500 square-foot Data Center following the relocation of its Crop Protection and Agrium Advanced Technologies (AAT) divisions to Loveland, CO.
• The budget is typically finalized in Q2.

IT Intelligence:

2013:
• 50-74% of its servers are to be virtualized by the end of 2013. 
• Corporate IT manages 10 mobile devices, while 90 are managed elsewhere, along with 100 desktops. 
• Data center strategy is centered on whatever is best for applications – VMs/standalone server/custom hardware appliance. 
• Long term plan for running new applications is to use location facilities and own hardware.





